	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001038_0001"/><!--pb/@n='49r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">3<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">d</hi></hi> June 
<lb/>1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p><persName>D<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Norton Shaw</persName>
<lb/>will I suppose be 
<lb/>a better hand for 
<lb/>looking over the 
<lb/>sheets than <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Galton</persName> and he 
<lb/>volunteered his 
<lb/>aid most frankly 
<lb/>when I asked him 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001038_0002"/><!--pb/@n='49v'--> 
<lb/>about <persName>Galton's</persName>
<lb/>qualifications. 
<lb/>He edits the journal 
<lb/>of the R.G.S. I should 
<lb/>like to get back the 
<lb/>corrections I sent 
<lb/>to the other man 
<lb/>if the slips are 
<lb/>not destroyed which 
<lb/>contained them<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I would like a 
<lb/>couple of wood cuts 
<lb/>to shew the form 
<lb/>of the fashion of 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001038_0003"/><!--pb/@n='50r'--> 
<lb/>dressing the hair 
<lb/>in London<reg>,</reg> one is 
<lb/>an imitation of 
<lb/>the glory round 
<lb/>the virgin<reg>'</reg>s head<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>If it can be done 
<lb/>I shall send you 
<lb/>a little drawing<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I shall bring 
<lb/>up two pieces of 
<lb/>manuscript tomorrow 
<lb/>got your note 
<lb/>yesterday. If you 
<lb/>are not as

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001038_0004"/><!--pb/@n='50v'--> 
<lb/>much vexed with 
<lb/>me as I was with 
<lb/>the revises I'm 
<lb/>mistaken. <choice><reg>Y</reg><orig>y</orig></choice>ou seem 
<lb/>as if about to say 
<lb/>"a plague upon the 
<lb/>fellow what does 
<lb/>he mean". I don<reg>'</reg>t 
<lb/>wonder at your 
<lb/>getting crusty with 
<lb/>me, but I can<reg>'</reg>t 
<lb/>muster a single grumble 
<lb/>at you in return<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">D. Livingstone</p><addSpan spanTo="#p49r-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left margin of f. 49r'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p>I have answered the enclosed. It need 
<lb/>not be preserved after you have read it</p><anchor xml:id="p49r-01"/>
			
